Good food, horrendous service and possible credit card fraud (check your statements).  Ordered food online on a Friday, but never received a confirmation email.  After about 15-20 mins, we called and the lady on the phone said they never received the online order.  So, we made the same order via phone.  30 mins go by, and we receive our email confirmation from the FIRST order.  We call again, and the same lady apologizes and says not to worry, they will cancel that order.  30 mins later, the delivery guy shows up with our food...and 10 mins after that, a SECOND delivery guy shows up with the same order.  I call Duccini's a 3rd time, and the same lady apologizes and guarantees I won't be charged twice (we sent the second delivery guy back with the food).  Today I check my online account, and low and behold TWO charges from Duccini's, and they are no longer "pending" (i.e. they are fully charged).  I filed a complaint with Chase, and will most likely need to call a 4th time to attempt to clear this up again.  Four phone calls and a headache for pizza and wings.  Also makes me wonder how two delivery drivers are sent to the same address within 10 mins of each other...I'm sensing there are some potential operating efficiencies to be gained at Duccini's...
